    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-04-11T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-04-11T06:00:00-05:00" n="638"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5622/4–1150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-04-11T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 11, 1950—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1094. Following is translation note referred my immediate preceding
                        telegram:<note n="1" xml:id="d638fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Government USSR considers it necessary to state following to Government
                        USA:</p>
                    <p>“According verified data, on 8 April this year at 17 hours 39 minutes, there
                        was observed south of Libava (Libau) a four-motored military airplane B–29
                        (Flying Fortress) with American identification signs, which went into
                        territory of Soviet Union for 21 kilometers. As American airplane continued
                        going deeper into Soviet territory, flight of Soviet fighters arose from
                        nearby airdrome, demanding that American airplane follow them for landing at
                        airdrome. American airplane not only did not submit to this demand, but
                        opened fire on Soviet airplanes. In view this, leading Soviet fighter was
                        compelled return fire, after which American airplane turned toward sea and
                        disappeared.</p>
                    <pb facs="1158" n="1142" xml:id="pg_1142"/>
                    <p>“Soviet Government states resolute protest to Government USA against gross
                        violation Soviet border by American military airplane, which is at same time
                        unheard of violation elementary standards International Law.</p>
                    <p>“Moscow, 11 April 1950”.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
